My wife and I went here for the first time this morning. We walked in to and empty restaurant. They sat us and handed us the menu. We were looking at the menu for no more than  3-5 minutes before I hear the manager say in Spanish what these people need more than 30 minutes to order? The hostess laughs along with the comment.  I'm an Argentine/Ecuadorian that speaks fluent Spanish. I understood this whole exchange and became extremely irritated and told my wife I didn't feel comfortable eating there . So we left . Running a restaurant that seems to be empty you should do everything possible to make your customers feel happy and welcome to repeat business and to spread word of a good restaurant. We regularly eat breakfast and like to find new places but this location is somewhere I definitely will never go back too.

Coming in to this place one can't help but notice and feel the very friendly staff. As soon as I walked in I was greeted with a big smile and hello, perhaps for some that's not very important but for someone like me, it just adds more to the experience. The inside is very nice with nice seating and spacious. One also has the option to sit out in the patio, which is something I didn't think could be nice, but as I stepped outside I was left mesmerized as they have a very nice space and a garden. Now on to the food, the food was really good, they always have breakfast anytime which is great as I like to get my breakfast around late in the afternoon. They have a Mexican corner in the menu, and quite frankly it was very good! I tried the steak tacos, and they were tasty, they come in three, and the best part is they are authentic Mexican tacos, just the more better. All in all, this place is definitely something I would recommend to everyone.
